---
By: Ralph W. Emerson
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 375
    Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Prayer
---
Prayer as a means to effect a private end is theft and meanness. It
supposes dualism in nature and consciousness. As soon as the man is one with
God he will not beg. He will then see prayer in all action.
